OL,3,CRise in people seeking help for
OL,4,Cpreviously little-known eating disorder
OL,6,FPatients with AFRID usually avoid
OL,7,Fcertain foods or limit what they eat.
OL,8,FThe can occur in children, teenagers
OL,9,Fand adults.
OL,11,FThis can happen for a number of
OL,12,Freasons, including sensitivity to
OL,13,Ftastes, textures, or smells,
OL,14,Fdistressing experiences while eating
OL,15,Fsuch as choking, and low interest in
OL,16,Ffood.
OL,18,FEating disorder charity Beat said its
OL,19,Fhelpline received more than 2,000
OL,20,Fphone calls in 2023, 10% of the total,
OL,21,Ffrom people seeking support for ARFID.
